Evidence for accelerated expansion of the universe is based on <b>distance measurements to type 1a supernova</b>&nbsp;using two methods.<br><ul><li>The&nbsp;<b>red shift method</b>&nbsp;- measure the red shift and use Hubble's law law to give the distance to each one.</li><li>The&nbsp;<b>luminosity method</b>&nbsp;- type 1a supernovae at&nbsp;<b>peak intensity</b>&nbsp;is known to be 10<sup>8</sup>&nbsp;times more luminous than the sun.</li></ul>